00:53:42,934 --> 00:53:47,373
At first, theyjust
grunted their refusal.

 713 
00:53:47,441 --> 00:53:49,876
But then,
on an historic day

 714 
00:53:49,944 --> 00:53:51,879
which is commemorated
by my species

 715 
00:53:51,947 --> 00:53:54,850
and fully documented
in the sacred scrolls,

 716 
00:53:54,919 --> 00:53:56,854
there came Aldo.

 717 
00:53:56,922 --> 00:53:59,448
He did not grunt.

 718 
00:53:59,525 --> 00:54:01,859
He articulated.

 719 
00:54:01,930 --> 00:54:05,526
He spoke a word which
had been spoken to him

 720 
00:54:05,601 --> 00:54:09,198
over time without number
by humans.

 721 
00:54:09,273 --> 00:54:12,244
He said...

 722 
00:54:12,312 --> 00:54:14,440
"No."

 723 
00:54:22,393 --> 00:54:24,589
So that's how
it all started.

 724 
00:54:26,366 --> 00:54:28,358
Clip one, please.

 725 
00:54:29,571 --> 00:54:33,669
Cornelius:
Where we come from, apes talk.

 726 
00:54:33,744 --> 00:54:35,679
Humans are dumb.

 727 
00:54:35,747 --> 00:54:38,547
You recognize your husband's words
to the commission?

 728 
00:54:38,619 --> 00:54:40,554
Yes.

 729 
00:54:40,622 --> 00:54:43,683
So humans were dumb.
Were they happy?

 730 
00:54:43,759 --> 00:54:45,694
Clip two.

 731 
00:54:45,762 --> 00:54:48,665
Zira:
As to humans, I've dissect--

 732 
00:54:48,734 --> 00:54:51,465
I've examined thousands of them.

 733 
00:54:51,538 --> 00:54:53,632
And until now,
I've only discovered

 734 
00:54:53,707 --> 00:54:55,642
2 who could talk in my life.

 735 
00:54:55,710 --> 00:54:59,239
Why did you change words
in the middle of a sentence?

 736 
00:54:59,316 --> 00:55:01,285
Repeat first three seconds
of clip two.

 737 
00:55:03,222 --> 00:55:07,753
Zira: As to humans,
I've dissect-- I've examined--

 738 
00:55:07,829 --> 00:55:11,129
- What was the word you didn't finish?
- I can't remember.

 739 
00:55:11,200 --> 00:55:14,069
- Play the loop.
- Zira: Dissect--Dissect--Dissect--

 740 
00:55:14,139 --> 00:55:16,370
- Complete the word, monkey.
- Look, I have told you--

 741 
00:55:16,442 --> 00:55:18,741
- Complete the word!
- Dissect--Dissect--Dissect--Dissect--

 742 
00:55:18,812 --> 00:55:20,644
Dissect--Dissect--Dissect--

 743 
00:55:20,715 --> 00:55:23,151
Sounds as if I had hiccups!

 744 
00:55:24,320 --> 00:55:26,482
[Laughing]

 745 
00:55:27,859 --> 00:55:29,794
Call for Dr. Dixon, please.

 746 
00:55:31,031 --> 00:55:35,129
Dr. Dixon?
Dr. Hasslein calling Dr. Dixon.

 747 
00:55:38,376 --> 00:55:40,311
P.A.:
Calling Dr. Dixon.

 748 
00:55:46,588 --> 00:55:49,820
Ah, Dr. Dixon. Come in.

 749 
00:55:58,106 --> 00:56:01,771
- Be good enough to administer
this to the female.
- Why? What is it?

 750 
00:56:01,845 --> 00:56:04,007
Sodium Pentothal.
1/2 gram l.V.

 751 
00:56:04,081 --> 00:56:07,712
- Dr. Hasslein,
I'm an animal psychiatrist.
- And a qualified vet, Dr. Dixon.

 752 
00:56:07,787 --> 00:56:10,382
You have
the commission's authority.

 753 
00:56:10,457 --> 00:56:13,656
And that of the president.
Please.

 754 
00:56:17,969 --> 00:56:21,634
Zira, I've been asked
to give you an injection--

 755 
00:56:21,708 --> 00:56:25,043
You can't use that! We only
use those things for killing.

 756 
00:56:25,113 --> 00:56:28,277
-Killing?
-No, this is not for killing, Cornelius.

 757 
00:56:28,351 --> 00:56:30,446
This is for relaxing.
It won't harm her.

 758 
00:56:30,522 --> 00:56:33,424
- Will it harm my baby?
- No, it won't.

 759 
00:56:33,492 --> 00:56:35,984
So, Zira, if you would
just come with me, please.

 760 
00:56:36,062 --> 00:56:38,555
Lewis, you can't
use that on Zira!

 761 
00:56:38,634 --> 00:56:42,094
- Please, take him to his quarters!
- Really.

 762 
00:56:42,173 --> 00:56:44,472
No, you mustn't!

 763 
00:56:45,844 --> 00:56:47,871
Zira! Zira!

 764 
00:56:56,694 --> 00:56:58,560
Please.

 765 
00:57:00,233 --> 00:57:02,202
Just lie down on the couch.

 766 
00:57:06,509 --> 00:57:09,105
And bare your arm, please.

 767 
00:57:09,180 --> 00:57:11,581
You don't have to tell me!

 768 
00:57:19,529 --> 00:57:24,059
This has the same effect
as grape juice plus.

 769 
00:57:37,422 --> 00:57:39,687
Now count backward from 1 0.

 770 
00:57:39,759 --> 00:57:42,161
1 0...9...

 771 
00:57:42,230 --> 00:57:44,199
8...7...

 772 
00:57:44,267 --> 00:57:47,203
6...5.

 773 
00:57:49,274 --> 00:57:50,970
4.

 774 
00:57:52,178 --> 00:57:54,841
What comes after 4?

 775 
00:57:54,915 --> 00:57:56,543
2.

 776 
00:57:59,423 --> 00:58:02,723
- Thank you, Dr. Dixon.
- It's customary to stay.

 777 
00:58:11,808 --> 00:58:15,246
- Zira.
- Hmm.

 778 
00:58:15,314 --> 00:58:18,307
You worked
in a room like this.

 779 
00:58:18,384 --> 00:58:20,250
Hmm...

 780 
00:58:21,323 --> 00:58:25,386
Bigger. Not so pretty.

 781 
00:58:25,462 --> 00:58:29,264
And there you practiced--

 782 
00:58:29,335 --> 00:58:32,238
Comparative.

 783 
00:58:32,306 --> 00:58:34,867
Comparative what?

 784 
00:58:34,943 --> 00:58:37,777
- An--an--an--
- Anatomy?

 785 
00:58:37,848 --> 00:58:41,786
- Anata--
- Whose anatomies did you compare?

 786 
00:58:41,854 --> 00:58:43,789
Apes and humans?

 787 
00:58:46,728 --> 00:58:50,195
Zira, say yes
if you mean yes.

 788 
00:58:51,331 --> 00:58:54,961
- Yes.
- So you dissected other apes?

 789 
00:58:55,036 --> 00:58:56,902
Ye--yes...

 790 
00:58:56,972 --> 00:59:00,910
when they died
a natural death.

 791 
00:59:00,979 --> 00:59:03,915
And humans, too, of course.

 792 
00:59:03,983 --> 00:59:05,815
Yes...

 793 
00:59:05,886 --> 00:59:09,255
as they were made available.

 794 
00:59:09,325 --> 00:59:14,493
- Available?
- Gorillas hunted them for sport

 795 
00:59:14,566 --> 00:59:17,297
in nets and with guns.

 796 
00:59:17,370 --> 00:59:20,535
The survivors were put in cages.

 797 
00:59:20,608 --> 00:59:24,512
The army used some
for target practice.

 798 
00:59:24,581 --> 00:59:27,676
We could pick from the rest.

 799 
00:59:27,752 --> 00:59:31,815
In the interest ofscience,
you dissected, removed,

 800 
00:59:31,892 --> 00:59:33,689
and statistically compared...

 801 
00:59:33,761 --> 00:59:37,962
bones, muscles, tendons,
veins, arteries,

 802 
00:59:38,035 --> 00:59:40,732
kidneys, livers, hearts,

 803 
00:59:40,805 --> 00:59:42,740
stomachs, reproductive organs,

 804 
00:59:42,808 --> 00:59:44,743
nails, tongues, eyes,

 805 
00:59:44,811 --> 00:59:48,044
noses, nervous systems,

 806 
00:59:48,117 --> 00:59:50,416
the various reflexes.

 807 
00:59:50,487 --> 00:59:52,353
Reflexes?

 808 
00:59:52,423 --> 00:59:54,358
Of the dead?

 809 
00:59:54,426 --> 00:59:58,489
No, no, no, no, no, no, no.
Of the living.

 810 
00:59:58,565 --> 01:00:01,866
You can't make
a dead man's knee jump

 811 
01:00:01,937 --> 01:00:06,968
any more than you can test
a corpse's reaction to a lobotomy.

 812 
01:00:07,046 --> 01:00:08,981
You were advanced enough

 813 
01:00:09,049 --> 01:00:12,987
to perform experimental
brain surgery on living humans?

 814 
01:00:13,055 --> 01:00:17,187
Oh, yes.
We even tried to stimulate

 815 
01:00:17,261 --> 01:00:20,198
their atrophied speech centers.

 816 
01:00:20,266 --> 01:00:22,326
Did you try to stimulate

 817 
01:00:22,402 --> 01:00:24,337
Colonel Taylor's speech centers?

 818 
01:00:24,405 --> 01:00:28,207
Of course not.
He could talk already.

 819 
01:00:28,278 --> 01:00:31,510
When you left,
was Colonel Taylor alive?

 820 
01:00:31,582 --> 01:00:34,644
We loved Taylor.

 821 
01:00:34,720 --> 01:00:38,715
We did all we could
to help him--

 822 
01:00:38,793 --> 01:00:40,887
Cornelius and l.

 823 
01:00:43,634 --> 01:00:45,569
Cornelius!

 824 
01:00:45,637 --> 01:00:47,572
She needs a nap.

 825 
01:00:47,640 --> 01:00:49,734
She'll get it.

 826 
01:00:53,816 --> 01:00:56,752
Orderly.

 827 
01:00:56,821 --> 01:01:01,260
- Sir?
- Take the female ape to its quarters.

 828 
01:01:01,328 --> 01:01:05,096
We must get this
to the commission.

 829 
01:01:05,234 --> 01:01:07,499
- [Bangs Gavel]
- Gentlemen, gentlemen.

 830 
01:01:07,570 --> 01:01:11,008
I've received an off cial notification
from the president

 831 
01:01:11,076 --> 01:01:14,012
ratify ing the final recommendations
made by this commission

 832 
01:01:14,080 --> 01:01:16,516
in light of
the tape recordings

 833 
01:01:16,584 --> 01:01:18,917
delivered by Dr. Hasslein.

 834 
01:01:18,988 --> 01:01:22,858
If you'll be seated,
we'll get down to business.

 835 
01:01:22,927 --> 01:01:26,365
Now, let me review
our conclusions.

 836 
01:01:26,432 --> 01:01:28,367
" 1 . By a majority vote,

 837 
01:01:28,435 --> 01:01:31,371
"the commission finds
no solid evidence for hostility

 838 
01:01:31,439 --> 01:01:34,376
"by either ape
towards the human race

 839 
01:01:34,444 --> 01:01:37,882
as it is presently constituted
in this year, 1 973."

 840 
01:01:37,950 --> 01:01:40,886
- I disagree--
- Let me remind you

 841 
01:01:40,954 --> 01:01:44,392
that this was
by a majority vote.

 842 
01:01:44,459 --> 01:01:46,394
"The male's attitude is that

 843 
01:01:46,462 --> 01:01:48,397
"of a deeply interested academician

 844 
01:01:48,465 --> 01:01:52,403
"who studied the alleged future
downfall of the human race

 845 
01:01:52,471 --> 01:01:55,442
"with the true objectivity
of a good historian.

 846 
01:01:55,510 --> 01:01:57,445
"The female's case is different,

 847 
01:01:57,513 --> 01:01:59,948
"in that she undoubtedly committed

 848 
01:02:00,016 --> 01:02:01,951
"actions against the human race

 849 
01:02:02,019 --> 01:02:04,922
"of a sort which,
if committed today,

 850 
01:02:04,991 --> 01:02:06,926
"would be called atrocities,

 851 
01:02:06,994 --> 01:02:10,932
"but would they be so called
in 2,000 years' time,

 852 
01:02:11,000 --> 01:02:13,435
"when it is alleged that humans

 853 
01:02:13,503 --> 01:02:15,438
"will have become dumb brutes

 854 
01:02:15,506 --> 01:02:17,441
"with the intelligence of animals?

 855 
01:02:17,509 --> 01:02:21,447
"It's been noted that
what apes will do to humans

 856 
01:02:21,515 --> 01:02:24,782
"is no more than what humans
now do to beasts.

 857 
01:02:24,854 --> 01:02:27,586
"Nonetheless,
the commission is sympathetic

 858 
01:02:27,659 --> 01:02:31,392
"to Dr. Hasslein's conviction
that these apes' progeny

 859 
01:02:31,465 --> 01:02:33,400
"could, in centuries to come,

 860 
01:02:33,468 --> 01:02:36,404
"prove an increasing threat
to the human race

 861 
01:02:36,472 --> 01:02:38,907
"and conceivably end
by dominating it.

 862 
01:02:38,975 --> 01:02:41,912
"This is a risk
we dare not ignore.

 863 
01:02:41,980 --> 01:02:44,415
"Therefore...

 864 
01:02:44,484 --> 01:02:48,013
"the commission
unanimously recommends

 865 
01:02:48,089 --> 01:02:51,026
"that the birth
of the female's unborn child

 866 
01:02:51,094 --> 01:02:52,824
"should be prevented

 867 
01:02:52,897 --> 01:02:55,628
"and that after
its prenatal removal,

 868 
01:02:55,701 --> 01:02:58,136
"both the male and the female

 869 
01:02:58,204 --> 01:03:00,436
"should humanely
be rendered incapable

 870 
01:03:00,509 --> 01:03:02,944
ofbearing another."

 871 
01:03:03,012 --> 01:03:06,245
I now declare
this commission dissolved.

 872 
01:03:06,384 --> 01:03:08,444
Savages!

 873 
01:03:08,521 --> 01:03:10,456
They are savages!

 874 
01:03:10,524 --> 01:03:13,460
Jabbing needles
into my pregnant wife.

 875 
01:03:13,528 --> 01:03:15,463
I've done that too, dear,

 876 
01:03:15,531 --> 01:03:17,967
and worse.

 877 
01:03:18,035 --> 01:03:22,474
Taylor thought
we were savages at first.

 878 
01:03:24,044 --> 01:03:27,413
Did they make you tell them
about Taylor too?

 879 
01:03:27,483 --> 01:03:32,479
They made me tell them
everyt hing, Cornelius.

 880 
01:03:32,557 --> 01:03:36,791
- Brutes.
- Shall I tell you something?

 881 
01:03:36,863 --> 01:03:41,098
I'm glad I did.
We can't live with lies.

 882 
01:03:41,170 --> 01:03:45,336
After this, I doubt
we shall be allowed to live at all.

 883 
01:03:47,480 --> 01:03:50,416
Do you mean that?

 884 
01:03:50,484 --> 01:03:52,419
Ohh...

 885 
01:03:54,491 --> 01:03:56,926
How long?

 886 
01:03:56,994 --> 01:03:59,156
A week.

 887 
01:03:59,231 --> 01:04:01,427
Maybe sooner.

 888 
01:04:01,501 --> 01:04:05,872
They treated you like dirt.

 889 
01:04:05,940 --> 01:04:09,207
- [Door Opens]
- Ma'am, sir.

 890 
01:04:09,279 --> 01:04:12,045
Chow time.

 891 
01:04:12,117 --> 01:04:14,052
I'm not hungry .

 892 
01:04:14,120 --> 01:04:18,786
Well, maybe somebody else is
who can't talk yet.

 893 
01:04:18,860 --> 01:04:21,797
Oh, come on, ma'am.
It's pure vitamin C.

 894 
01:04:21,865 --> 01:04:23,800
You better drink the soup
and eat the oranges

 895 
01:04:23,868 --> 01:04:27,203
- for that little monkey--
- Grr!

 896 
01:04:27,274 --> 01:04:29,209
What have you done,
Cornelius?

 897 
01:04:29,277 --> 01:04:32,213
Nobody makes a fool
out ofmy wife.

 898 
01:04:32,281 --> 01:04:34,216
We just ought to leave.

 899 
01:04:59,655 --> 01:05:02,592
I'll be going back
with Dr. Hasslein soon.

 900 
01:05:02,660 --> 01:05:04,856
I have to tell them.

 901 
01:05:04,930 --> 01:05:08,698
- You've got to come help me.
- I'll come right away.

 902 
01:05:08,769 --> 01:05:12,969
Itjust seems so cruel
and horrible and-- I don't know.

 903 
01:05:13,042 --> 01:05:15,034
I'll see you.

 904 
01:05:17,115 --> 01:05:20,553
- Cruel, Dr. Dixon?
- Unbelievably.

 905 
01:05:20,621 --> 01:05:22,715
Zira wants her baby.

 906 
01:05:22,790 --> 01:05:25,454
- So do l.
- But dead.

 907 
01:05:25,529 --> 01:05:29,934
- Yes.
- You'd prefer the parents dead too.

 908 
01:05:30,002 --> 01:05:32,130
Shall we go?

 909 
01:05:51,568 --> 01:05:53,662
[Telephone Rings]

 910 
01:05:55,073 --> 01:06:00,013
Gate four.Just a minute, sir.
I'll take a look.

 911 
01:06:00,081 --> 01:06:03,313
No, sir. The lieutenant
hasn't checked in yet.

 912 
01:06:04,821 --> 01:06:07,690
- Good night, Charlie.
- Night, Ed.

 913 
01:06:07,759 --> 01:06:10,695
Yes, sir.
I'll give him that message.

 914 
01:06:10,763 --> 01:06:14,030
"Contact the motor pool."
As soon as I see him.

 915 
01:06:14,102 --> 01:06:16,037
[Hangs Up Telephone]

 916 
01:06:16,105 --> 01:06:19,041
- [Telephone Rings]
- Gate four.

 917 
01:06:19,109 --> 01:06:21,044
Oh, yes, Captain.

 918 
01:06:22,214 --> 01:06:25,447
The supply truck isn't
due until 0600 hours.

 919 
01:06:27,189 --> 01:06:30,318
- Well, I'm sorry , sir.
- Good night, Charlie.

 920 
01:06:30,393 --> 01:06:32,658
I said, "good night."

 921 
01:06:32,731 --> 01:06:35,223
We can't contact them
until then.

 922 
01:06:35,301 --> 01:06:37,566
Well, the depot's closed, sir.

 923 
01:06:37,638 --> 01:06:39,903
Okay, sir.
I'll be off duty,

 924 
01:06:39,974 --> 01:06:42,809
but the relief
comes on at 0430 hours.

 925 
01:06:42,879 --> 01:06:46,624
I'll have him pass
the message. Yes, sir.

 926 
01:07:05,553 --> 01:07:07,488
Zira, what's the matter?

 927 
01:07:09,559 --> 01:07:11,494
I...

 928 
01:07:11,562 --> 01:07:14,498
I think my pains have begun.

 929 
01:07:14,566 --> 01:07:16,501
Oh, my dear.

 930 
01:07:31,426 --> 01:07:33,987
Administration, Doctor.
It's urgent.

 931 
01:08:05,143 --> 01:08:07,443
- What happened?
- The apes killed their orderly.

 932 
01:08:07,514 --> 01:08:10,075
- Where are they?
- On the run.

 933 
01:08:10,151 --> 01:08:13,281
Now they've killed.
For that, they must be killed.

 934 
01:08:13,356 --> 01:08:16,190
It has to be done
before we start a stone rolling

 935 
01:08:16,260 --> 01:08:20,596
that'll gather enough
poison moss to kill us all!

 936 
01:08:34,755 --> 01:08:37,247
Look.
I'll go back to camp.

 937 
01:08:37,325 --> 01:08:41,491
- I'll find Lewis and get help.
- No. No.

 938 
01:08:41,565 --> 01:08:44,297
I just lost my temper
with the boy.

 939 
01:08:44,370 --> 01:08:48,399
- It's better now. I can walk.
- Listen to me.

 940 
01:08:48,476 --> 01:08:50,638
They may punish us
for what we did,

 941 
01:08:50,712 --> 01:08:53,546
but at least the baby
will be born.

 942 
01:09:29,271 --> 01:09:32,572
- Were they armed?
- No, I don't believe so.

 943 
01:09:32,643 --> 01:09:36,581
Then there's no need
for a shooting match.

 944 
01:09:36,649 --> 01:09:38,584
Not strictly speaking.

 945 
01:09:38,652 --> 01:09:40,587
I am speaking strictly,
Hasslein.

 946 
01:09:40,655 --> 01:09:42,886
Science regards
these apes as unique.

 947 
01:09:42,958 --> 01:09:45,484
People regard them
as practically human.

 948 
01:09:45,562 --> 01:09:47,998
The killers of today
could become

 949 
01:09:48,066 --> 01:09:50,160
the mass murderers of tomorrow.

 950 
01:09:50,236 --> 01:09:53,674
I can think ofno one
better equipped emotionally

 951 
01:09:53,742 --> 01:09:56,678
to persuade the people
of that possibility,

 952 
01:09:56,746 --> 01:09:59,683
but, in a democracy,
we do not shoot

 953 
01:09:59,751 --> 01:10:02,687
unarmed suspects on sight
for a murder

 954 
01:10:02,755 --> 01:10:05,692
in which their participation
is still legally unproven.

 955 
01:10:05,760 --> 01:10:09,254
I want them taken, yes,
but taken alive.

 956 
01:10:09,332 --> 01:10:11,198
Is that clear?

 957 
01:10:11,268 --> 01:10:13,362
Quite clear, Mr. President.

 958 
01:10:44,251 --> 01:10:46,186
You lost, miss?

 959 
01:10:46,254 --> 01:10:48,189
Oh, it's you, Dr. Branton.

 960 
01:10:48,257 --> 01:10:50,624
Be careful.
There's been a murder.

 961 
01:10:50,694 --> 01:10:54,826
- Murder?
- The monkeys have killed
their orderly and escaped.

 962 
01:10:54,900 --> 01:10:58,338
What? I don't believe it.
How did it happen?

 963 
01:10:58,406 --> 01:11:01,343
All I know is they've
killed their orderly,

 964 
01:11:01,411 --> 01:11:05,679
And I've been given orders
to find them. Drive carefully.

 965 
01:11:05,751 --> 01:11:09,154
There will be a lot
ofvehicles in the area.

 966 
01:11:33,459 --> 01:11:35,394
Cornelius, what have you done?

 967 
01:11:35,462 --> 01:11:37,898
I didn't mean to kill him.

 968 
01:11:37,966 --> 01:11:40,401
He was teasing Zira.
I hit him with a tray.

 969 
01:11:40,470 --> 01:11:44,101
- Please believe me.
- I do, Cornelius, but they won't.

 970 
01:11:44,176 --> 01:11:48,842
- Where's Zira?
- She's back there.
She's hiding in the bushes.

 971 
01:11:48,916 --> 01:11:51,182
Stevie... she's in labor.

 972 
01:11:51,253 --> 01:11:54,951
Oh, God. Get in.

 973 
01:12:00,935 --> 01:12:05,374
Stevie, you won't
take us back to the camp?

 974 
01:12:05,441 --> 01:12:08,879
Get down.
I have a better idea.

 975 
01:12:24,637 --> 01:12:27,972
Now, wait a second.
Just a moment.

 976 
01:12:28,042 --> 01:12:29,977
Let me get this straight.

 977 
01:12:30,045 --> 01:12:32,981
You are asking me
to risk imprisonment

 978 
01:12:33,049 --> 01:12:35,918
for the sake of two
fugitive apes?

 979 
01:12:35,988 --> 01:12:39,426
The answer is
a thousand times... yes.

 980 
01:12:39,493 --> 01:12:42,429
Oh, yes.
I do it for you

 981 
01:12:42,497 --> 01:12:44,432
and for Stevie

 982 
01:12:44,500 --> 01:12:46,935
and for your two
distinguished friends.

 983 
01:12:47,004 --> 01:12:50,442
- Uh, notorious now.
- The hell with notoriety.

 984 
01:12:50,509 --> 01:12:53,446
What is a husband
expected to do?

 985 
01:12:53,514 --> 01:12:56,450
Stand by and see
his wife insulted?

 986 
01:12:56,518 --> 01:12:59,455
Aren't we rude
enough to each other

 987 
01:12:59,523 --> 01:13:02,459
without having to be
rude to animals?

 988 
01:13:02,527 --> 01:13:05,464
Anyway, he didn't mean
to kill the boy.

 989 
01:13:05,532 --> 01:13:07,558
Los trato bien, muchachos?

 990 
01:13:07,635 --> 01:13:10,401
Si, patron. Salud!

 991 
01:13:10,473 --> 01:13:12,908
I sure appreciate
what you're doing.

 992 
01:13:12,977 --> 01:13:15,412
You helped deliver
our last baby.

 993 
01:13:15,480 --> 01:13:17,915
Now you will deliver our next.

 994 
01:13:24,061 --> 01:13:27,498
Lewis!
What took you so long?

 995 
01:13:27,565 --> 01:13:30,365
I had to make some excuse.
They think I'm searching.

 996 
01:13:30,437 --> 01:13:34,842
- Armando's been a saint.
- Saint Francis would have
fixed it better.

 997 
01:13:34,910 --> 01:13:39,042
- Never.
- Say hello to Heloise

 998 
01:13:39,116 --> 01:13:41,814
and your goddaughter Salome.

 999 
01:13:41,887 --> 01:13:46,258
- Hello, Salome.
- The first chimp ever born in a circus.

 1000 
01:13:46,327 --> 01:13:48,159
Los Angeles has had four.

 1001 
01:13:48,230 --> 01:13:51,429
Los Angeles isn't a circus.
It's a zoo.

 1002 
01:13:51,502 --> 01:13:53,437
So New Yorkers say.

 1003 
01:13:53,505 --> 01:13:55,599
Lewis is here.

 1004 
01:13:55,675 --> 01:13:58,612
Lewis, I was not responsible
for the death--

 1005 
01:13:58,680 --> 01:14:04,120
I know, but you will be responsible
for a birth. How is she?

 1006 
01:14:04,187 --> 01:14:06,521
The pains are coming
every five minutes.

 1007 
01:14:06,592 --> 01:14:09,084
Every four.

 1008 
01:14:09,162 --> 01:14:11,358
[Chattering]

 1009 
01:14:11,432 --> 01:14:15,894
- Look. Look at Heloise.
- [Baby Chattering]

 1010 
01:14:15,973 --> 01:14:18,807
She's showing an expectant mother
what to expect.

 1011 
01:14:18,877 --> 01:14:21,369
Mama. Mama.

 1012 
01:14:21,447 --> 01:14:24,384
Say it. Mama.

 1013 
01:14:24,452 --> 01:14:26,478
- Mama.
- Zira.

 1014 
01:14:26,555 --> 01:14:28,490
Zira, don't waste your breath.

 1015 
01:14:28,558 --> 01:14:31,495
You know the child
of two primitive apes

 1016 
01:14:31,563 --> 01:14:34,499
will never learn how to speak.

 1017 
01:14:34,567 --> 01:14:36,502
I'm getting into practice.

 1018 
01:14:36,570 --> 01:14:39,507
Mama. Mama.

 1019 
01:14:39,575 --> 01:14:42,743
Mam--
[Moaning]

 1020 
01:14:49,955 --> 01:14:51,890
There. That's good.

 1021 
01:14:54,461 --> 01:14:56,396
Come on. Over here.

 1022 
01:15:04,477 --> 01:15:06,912
What are we going to call...

 1023 
01:15:06,981 --> 01:15:09,416
- Him.
- him?

 1024 
01:15:09,484 --> 01:15:11,419
Milo?

 1025 
01:15:14,492 --> 01:15:16,427
Milo.

 1026 
01:15:17,496 --> 01:15:19,431
Milo.

 1027 
01:15:24,007 --> 01:15:26,943
- Milo.
- Congratulations.

 1028 
01:15:27,011 --> 01:15:28,946
Oh.

 1029 
01:15:31,017 --> 01:15:32,952
[Coughing]

 1030 
01:15:33,020 --> 01:15:35,354
- No?
- No.

 1031 
01:15:55,588 --> 01:15:59,026
- But, sir--
- Captain, I'm aware
that you've canvassed

 1032 
01:15:59,093 --> 01:16:01,028
the areas we first established.

 1033 
01:16:01,096 --> 01:16:04,534
Evidently, we were wrong
because you haven't found them!

 1034 
01:16:04,602 --> 01:16:07,697
Thank you.
Dr. Dixon, can you pinpoint

 1035 
01:16:07,772 --> 01:16:11,107
the probable date of the baby's birth
with any degree of accuracy?

 1036 
01:16:11,178 --> 01:16:14,843
Well, I never examined her,
but from appearances

 1037 
01:16:14,917 --> 01:16:17,113
I'd say a week to 1 0 days.

 1038 
01:16:17,187 --> 01:16:19,953
If that's close,
she can't have gone far.

 1039 
01:16:20,025 --> 01:16:22,051
- Where do apes go?
- To other apes.

 1040 
01:16:25,132 --> 01:16:30,539
Of course. Captain, I want you
to start an immediate search

 1041 
01:16:30,607 --> 01:16:33,305
ofevery menagerie,
zoo, and circus.

 1042 
01:16:33,379 --> 01:16:35,473
I'll augment your force
with the city police,

 1043 
01:16:35,548 --> 01:16:39,850
and I want to be kept informed
about all results.

 1044 
01:16:39,921 --> 01:16:43,222
- Yes, sir.
- [Door Closes]

 1045 
01:16:46,766 --> 01:16:49,429
- Lewis will think ofsomething.
- I am so sorry .

 1046 
01:16:49,503 --> 01:16:51,369
I had planned it so well.

 1047 
01:16:51,439 --> 01:16:55,434
In one month, we move on
to our winter quarters in Florida.

 1048 
01:16:55,512 --> 01:16:58,506
I could have released you
in the Everglades.

 1049 
01:16:58,583 --> 01:17:02,487
You might have lived
happily ever af ter.

 1050 
01:17:02,556 --> 01:17:04,991
But now...
what can I do?

 1051 
01:17:05,060 --> 01:17:08,498
You have done enough
to make us grateful forever.

 1052 
01:17:08,565 --> 01:17:13,004
I did it because
I like chimpanzees best of all apes,

 1053 
01:17:13,072 --> 01:17:16,407
and you,
the best of all chimpanzees.

 1054 
01:17:17,979 --> 01:17:21,940
I did it because I hate those
who try to alter destiny

 1055 
01:17:22,019 --> 01:17:25,080
which is the unalterable
will ofGod.

 1056 
01:17:25,157 --> 01:17:27,092
Ifit is man's destiny

 1057 
01:17:27,160 --> 01:17:29,095
one day to be dominated,

 1058 
01:17:29,163 --> 01:17:31,530
Iet him be dominated by you.

 1059 
01:17:33,436 --> 01:17:36,668
All I can now do
to help you

 1060 
01:17:36,742 --> 01:17:40,680
is give you this
for the baby.

 1061 
01:17:40,748 --> 01:17:44,516
It's a medal of
Saint Francis of assisi.

 1062 
01:17:44,587 --> 01:17:47,853
- Who is he?
- He was a holy man

 1063 
01:17:47,924 --> 01:17:50,360
who loved and cared for animals.

 1064 
01:17:50,429 --> 01:17:52,864
- Yes.
- Oh, thank you.

 1065 
01:17:52,932 --> 01:17:55,697
We'll hang it around
the baby's neck

 1066 
01:17:55,770 --> 01:17:57,705
for protection, huh?

 1067 
01:17:57,773 --> 01:18:00,744
- Thank you.
- Yes.

 1068 
01:18:00,811 --> 01:18:03,246
And now, my dear,
dear friends,

 1069 
01:18:03,314 --> 01:18:07,252
before the police come
and the audience gathers,

 1070 
01:18:07,320 --> 01:18:09,722
you and your pretty baby must go.

 1071 
01:18:09,792 --> 01:18:11,727
Lewis is on his way.

 1072 
01:18:11,795 --> 01:18:14,560
- Armando.
- Yes?

 1073 
01:18:14,632 --> 01:18:18,400
I should like to say good-bye
to Heloise first.

 1074 
01:18:18,471 --> 01:18:21,772
Ifshe could speak,
she'd say she's sorry .

 1075 
01:18:21,843 --> 01:18:25,611
I know, but we
understand each other.

 1076 
01:18:28,753 --> 01:18:30,688
All right.
All right.

 1077 
01:19:30,915 --> 01:19:34,283
This is as far
as we dare to take you.

 1078 
01:19:34,352 --> 01:19:37,846
The police have roadblocks
on every main exit.

 1079 
01:19:37,925 --> 01:19:40,190
- Here are your supplies.
- Thank you.

 1080 
01:19:40,262 --> 01:19:42,231
Can you read a map?

 1081 
01:19:42,299 --> 01:19:45,736
I'm an archaeologist.
I can even draw one.

 1082 
01:19:47,806 --> 01:19:49,741
We're at the city limits

 1083 
01:19:49,809 --> 01:19:52,746
at the southern edge
of this oil field.

 1084 
01:19:52,814 --> 01:19:55,249
Over this hill,
you'll pass through

 1085 
01:19:55,318 --> 01:19:57,754
more oil wells,
an abandoned refinery ,

 1086 
01:19:57,822 --> 01:20:00,758
and you'll be looking
down at a harbor.

 1087 
01:20:00,826 --> 01:20:03,261
It's a graveyard
for old ships.

 1088 
01:20:03,330 --> 01:20:05,766
I played there as a kid.

 1089 
01:20:05,834 --> 01:20:08,770
There's a derelict tanker
at one end.

 1090 
01:20:08,838 --> 01:20:11,069
- You can hide there for a week.
- A week?

 1091 
01:20:11,142 --> 01:20:15,444
Until the commotion dies down and
we can smuggle you back to the circus.

 1092 
01:20:15,515 --> 01:20:18,850
Then you can travel
with them to Florida,

 1093 
01:20:18,921 --> 01:20:22,517
found a colony in the Everglades,
and live happily ever after.

 1094 
01:20:22,592 --> 01:20:24,288
[Baby Cry ing]

 1095 
01:20:24,362 --> 01:20:26,798
Mama. Mama.

 1096 
01:20:26,866 --> 01:20:28,801
Mama.

 1097 
01:20:32,375 --> 01:20:35,243
It's time that
you were moving on.

 1098 
01:20:37,882 --> 01:20:40,785
- Lewis.
- Yes?

 1099 
01:20:40,854 --> 01:20:45,885
If they find us,
we shall be killed?

 1100 
01:20:48,899 --> 01:20:50,765
Ultimately.

 1101 
01:20:52,338 --> 01:20:55,331
Then, uh...give us
the opportunity

 1102 
01:20:55,409 --> 01:20:57,344
to kill ourselves

 1103 
01:20:57,412 --> 01:21:00,474
if that moment should come.

 1104 
01:21:02,887 --> 01:21:05,414
Please.

 1105 
01:21:08,529 --> 01:21:10,464
I shouldn't do this,

 1106 
01:21:10,532 --> 01:21:13,526
but I guessed you might ask.

 1107 
01:21:20,447 --> 01:21:23,714
You're the second human
I've kissed.

 1108 
01:21:29,461 --> 01:21:32,398
And you are the first.

 1109 
01:21:38,975 --> 01:21:41,376
Come along, Zira.
Now, don't dawdle.

 1110 
01:22:24,545 --> 01:22:26,480
The ape with the kid?

 1111 
01:22:26,548 --> 01:22:29,484
She's been with
the circus seven years now.

 1112 
01:22:29,552 --> 01:22:32,489
The baby's birth was
registered 1 6 days ago.

 1113 
01:22:32,557 --> 01:22:34,492
Look how he's growing.

 1114 
01:22:34,560 --> 01:22:38,794
The first chimpanzee
ever to be born in a circus!

 1115 
01:22:38,866 --> 01:22:41,803
Do you realize what
a distinction that is?

 1116 
01:22:41,871 --> 01:22:45,513
It's like being
the first fish born on land.

 1117 
01:22:45,648 --> 01:22:49,916
- Nothing.
- It's like being the first bird
born without an egg,

 1118 
01:22:49,988 --> 01:22:53,117
the first baby born
on the moon.

 1119 
01:22:53,192 --> 01:22:55,287
It's like being--

 1120 
01:22:58,200 --> 01:23:00,533
Ha ha ha!

 1121 
01:23:00,603 --> 01:23:02,469
Negative! Negative!
Negative!

 1122 
01:23:02,539 --> 01:23:04,633
We'll catch them
sooner or later.

 1123 
01:23:04,709 --> 01:23:07,145
Later we'll do something
about pollution.

 1124 
01:23:07,214 --> 01:23:10,150
Later we'll do something
about the population explosion.

 1125 
01:23:10,218 --> 01:23:13,155
Later we'll do something
about nuclear war.

 1126 
01:23:13,223 --> 01:23:17,161
We think we've got all
the time in the world!

 1127 
01:23:17,229 --> 01:23:20,165
How much time
has the world got?

 1128 
01:23:20,233 --> 01:23:23,033
Somebody has to
begin to care.

 1129 
01:23:37,326 --> 01:23:40,263
Ah! Like stars in space.

 1130 
01:23:40,331 --> 01:23:42,766
Isn't it beautiful?

 1131 
01:23:42,834 --> 01:23:44,769
Yes, it is...

 1132 
01:23:44,837 --> 01:23:46,772
from here.

 1133 
01:23:47,842 --> 01:23:49,777
Well...ha ha ha!

 1134 
01:23:49,845 --> 01:23:51,780
We must move on.

 1135 
01:23:53,851 --> 01:23:55,786
Hmm...

 1136 
01:24:10,376 --> 01:24:12,311
[Baby Cry ing]

 1137 
01:25:06,628 --> 01:25:09,564
- Who found it?
- The field superintendent.

 1138 
01:25:09,632 --> 01:25:13,570
Routine service check.
It was hidden in the workings.

 1139 
01:25:13,638 --> 01:25:16,803
- She didn't need this anymore.
- Why don't we get moving?

 1140 
01:25:16,877 --> 01:25:20,645
- We've called in for helicopters.
- How long till they get here?

 1141 
01:25:20,716 --> 01:25:22,844
20 minutes.
They're running down

 1142 
01:25:22,919 --> 01:25:26,186
a fire report
in the Simi Valley.

 1143 
01:25:26,258 --> 01:25:29,194
- Keep me posted.
- Yes, sir.

 1144 
01:25:47,023 --> 01:25:50,721
- What's the matter?
- They found Zira's suitcase.

 1145 
01:25:53,466 --> 01:25:55,401
[Horn Honks]

 1146 
01:27:44,667 --> 01:27:47,832
Did Lewis really play here?

 1147 
01:27:47,906 --> 01:27:51,105
It was probably cleaner then.

 1148 
01:27:51,178 --> 01:27:53,739
It stinks... ofman.

 1149 
01:27:53,815 --> 01:27:56,342
Oh, no, no, no.

 1150 
01:27:56,419 --> 01:27:59,446
That's oil and dead fish.

 1151 
01:27:59,523 --> 01:28:02,460
Is that what man
wanted oil for--

 1152 
01:28:02,528 --> 01:28:04,759
to kill fish?

 1153 
01:28:05,833 --> 01:28:08,929
You don't like them
very much, do you?

 1154 
01:28:09,004 --> 01:28:13,033
- Who?
- Humans.

 1155 
01:28:13,111 --> 01:28:17,277
We've met hundreds
since we've been here,

 1156 
01:28:17,350 --> 01:28:20,515
and I trust...

 1157 
01:28:20,589 --> 01:28:22,524
three.

 1158 
01:28:29,870 --> 01:28:32,806
Mama. Mama.

 1159 
01:28:32,874 --> 01:28:34,809
Mama.

 1160 
01:28:36,212 --> 01:28:38,147
He wants feeding.

 1161 
01:28:38,215 --> 01:28:40,309
Oh, yes, well, um...

 1162 
01:28:41,888 --> 01:28:45,155
there must be someplace
cleaner than this.

 1163 
01:28:46,729 --> 01:28:48,664
I'll look around.

 1164 
01:31:32,519 --> 01:31:34,454
Zira:
Cornelius?

 1165 
01:31:53,550 --> 01:31:56,817
Cornelius?

 1166 
01:31:59,125 --> 01:32:02,756
I see you've had
your baby, Zira.

 1167 
01:32:02,831 --> 01:32:06,633
The Presidential Commission has
empowered me to take it in my care.

 1168 
01:32:08,807 --> 01:32:11,038
Give it to me.

 1169 
01:32:14,816 --> 01:32:16,751
[Baby Chattering]

 1170 
01:32:35,848 --> 01:32:38,148
Cornelius!

 1171 
01:33:20,415 --> 01:33:22,350
[Tires Screeching]

 1172 
01:33:34,570 --> 01:33:37,506
Spread your men out
along the pier!

 1173 
01:33:37,574 --> 01:33:39,509
All right, men!
Move out!

 1174 
01:33:39,577 --> 01:33:42,946
- Get them down there!
- Move! Move! Go!

 1175 
01:33:43,016 --> 01:33:45,042
Down to the end!

 1176 
01:33:45,119 --> 01:33:47,213
All right! Let's go!

 1177 
01:33:47,289 --> 01:33:49,953
[Tires Screeching]

 1178 
01:34:06,618 --> 01:34:08,553
Stevie.

 1179 
01:34:22,275 --> 01:34:24,541
Zira.

 1180 
01:34:24,613 --> 01:34:27,879
I want that baby. If you won't
give it to me, I'll shoot.

 1181 
01:34:32,458 --> 01:34:34,222
[Baby Shrieks]

 1182 
01:34:36,431 --> 01:34:38,627
My God! Stop him!

 1183 
01:34:38,701 --> 01:34:41,569
[Gunshot]

 1184 
01:34:41,638 --> 01:34:43,573
Aah!

 1185 
01:34:46,479 --> 01:34:48,778
- [Gunshots]
- No!

 1186 
01:34:54,992 --> 01:34:57,258
[Gasping]

 1187 
01:35:03,072 --> 01:35:05,974
Keep your men here!
Come on!

 1188 
01:35:14,354 --> 01:35:16,449
Zira!

 1189 
01:35:19,196 --> 01:35:21,131
What's she doing?

 1190 
01:35:25,371 --> 01:35:27,306
Oh, my God.

 1191 
01:35:54,149 --> 01:35:57,086
Armando:
All hands on the guy lines.

 1192 
01:35:57,154 --> 01:36:00,090
